§T
Tree punching does not seem to work at all! I should collect some rocks for some basic tools first.


§7With the §9No Tree Punching §7mod, wood is gotten through other means than direct contact with fists. The goal is to collect enough materials to make a §eFlint Hatchet§7.
§6§6

I have awoken in the middle of nowhere. Is this a dream? Is this real life? At any rate, I hope I still remember who I am...


§7Use the §9LevelUp! Reloaded §eSkill Book §7given to pick a desired class. By default, §6B§7 is the keybind for the skill menu.

I should try and get some branches from trees. Bamboo and reeds would serve as well.


§7Broken §eLeaf Blocks§7 have a chance to drop sticks.

I can attach this shard of flint to a handle to make a §eFlint Knife§f, which is great for harvesting plant fibres!


§7Comes in various materials as well such as diamond, copper, and iron.

If I smash these rocks together, I might be able to form a sharp edge. Alternatively, I could try and dig up some flint.


§7Put §t§2three §7of any rock in the crafting grid to get a flint shard. This is also a great way to get started with the §9Just Enough Items§7 GUI; Press §6U§7 to see recipes requiring a material. Try that on the rock.

All types of dirt, grass, farmland, and sand blocks can drop §eFlint Shards§7. This is another way of getting flint, but relies on random chance instead.

I should be able to recover some leather by cutting it up.


§7§9No Tree Punching §7§e§7§eKnives§7 can be used to get leather back from 100% durability leather gear. Simply have the gear to be recycled in the §6off-hand §7slot, then §6right click§7 with the knife.
I need an axe to chop down a tree! Get to it!

I should be able to turn some of this plant fibre into twine.


§7Craft some §ePlant String §7from plant fibre. This has the exact same uses as vanilla string.

I can gather §ePlant Fibres §fefficiently with a knife now! Better to get a lot of it...

§7
§6Left click§7 and destroy tall grass with a knife.
§7Knives from the §9Roots§7 and §9Mystical World§7 mods can also be used to harvest §ePlant Fibres §7from grass.

Finally!


§7With §9Tree Chopper§7, hold down shift and break a §eblock of wood §7with an §eaxe item §7(axe, battleaxe, mattock) to chop down the entire tree at once. You'll know that this works if the block is broken at a slower rate than normal. This will not work for §22§7§7x§22§7§7 thick trees (dark oak, jungle), so just chop each wood block individually in that case.

betterquesting:10.name:8: No Wood Plank Crafting?! What a [redacted] Piece of [redacted]
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
My disappointment is immeasurable, and my day is ruined.


§7§7Follow this procedure:

1. Place down §eLog Blocks §7in a row, with no other block covering the top of any log.

2. §6Right Click§7 each §eLog Block§7§7's §eTop Surface§7 with an axe item in hand (axe, battleaxe, mattock).

§m3. Profit


§7To get §eSticks§7 from §eWooden Planks§7, follow the same procedure but place down §eWooden Planks §7instead.
§7What more is there to say?

I should craft a §eRudimentary Pickaxe §f§ffor excavating the basic §eOres §fand digging all kinds of §eStone§f.


§7Acquiring §eANY §7of these items will complete the task.

I should be able to use flax fibres to my advantage when I encounter them in the wild!


§7Can harvest §eString§7 from §9Biome O' Plenty§7's flax plant when broken with any §eKnife§7 item in hand.

A rope coil... Should help me get around, especially into unknown areas deep below the surface!


§7The rope coil can be placed on the §6bottom of a block§7. Once this first segment of rope is placed, right clicking the rope with more rope coil in hand will extend the coil downwards. The rope coil acts as a solid block §eLadder §7that can be climbed from all directions at once.

It seems that some of my tools and equipment come with a modifier! I wonder if there's any way to change them later.

§7The §9Quality Tools§7 § §7mod adds many different trinket and tool qualities into the game, all of which are picked from a randomized list. Better modifiers are weighted less but provide very significant bonuses. On the other hand, there are (really) bad qualities that render the item ineffective. All qualities can be rerolled on a §ereforging station§7§7§7 with a reforge material. More details on that later.

Equipped §ebaubles and trinkets§7 can have an additional modifier as provided by §9Bountiful Baubles§7. They work the exact same way except need to be rerolled with experience instead of materials on a §etrinket reforging station§7.

§aGreen§7 qualities are unique to a specific item and cannot be reforged! Typically these are rare drops from mobs or crafted.

A matchbox should help me get a fire started.


§7§7This does the exact same thing as a §eFlint and Steel§7, which lights a §eFire§7 (that spreads).

A stone pickaxe would be great!


§7You'll notice that the stone pickaxe, unlike a wooden one, has a skill requirement from §9Reskillable§7. This mod gates many tools behind the §2eight§7 main skills, so get familiar with them. To access the §eSkills Menu§7, you have §2two §7§7options:


1. §7The default keybind is §6Y§7.

2.§7 Open inventory, then find the §eBag-like Icon§7 at the far left. the §eSkills Menu§7 is immediately below.


You must invest §aexperience§7 into each skill to level it up. To get to the next level, you need to spend as much §aexperience§7 as it takes to reach that level. 

Example: You want §fMining 2§7. This means that you'll need at least §a2 §7full levels of §aexperience§7 before you can invest to improve §fMining§7. If you happened to be §aexperience level 4,§7 then upgrading will take away exactly the §aamount of §aexperience §7(not flat levels) needed to reach §alevel 2§7, no more and no less.

A furnace! I can do a lot with this.


§7

I should probably get some better tools. Stone is a great starting place for that!


§7While mining stone, only §eRocks§7 will drop. Craft these rocks back into §eCobblestone§7.

Picked up §eRocks§7 scattered everywhere can be used as well.

Something has definitely changed, yet I don't know exactly what that is...


§9First Aid § §7provides a more realistic and hardcore experience. It makes the game more visceral and dangerous when paired with §9Enhanced Visuals§7, which adds visual effects such as blood splatters, and §9Dynamic Surroundings§7, which adds lots of ambient sounds such as chirping birds and the clinks of chainmail when you run.

Natural health regeneration is on, but at a greatly reduced rate. Healing consumables such as §eElixirs §7and §eSalves§7, §eHealing Spells§7 and §eBaubles§7 are key to survival.

§7Press §6H§7 and listen to the §9First Aid §7mod tutorial.

§fI will need to diversify my diet to survive and thrive.


§7Press §6N§7 to access the nutrition GUI or by clicking the §eCarrot Icon§7 in the inventory.

§7The §9Nutrition §7mod introduces different food groups that each food item belongs to. When each nutrition reaches a threshold, then a §eBuff §7will be granted as long as all food group nutrition values are maintained beyond the threshold.

Dying will cause each nutrition value to drop by a set amount, so smart play is encouraged instead of reckless displays of bravado.

Eating at maximum hunger is §f§lallowed§7. Use this to top up on hunger before a fight, or simply just to refill nutrition when lacking.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Toto, We're Not in Kansas Anymore...
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
I have a bad feeling about this place... It seems so calm and nice, but I don't like it one bit...


§7Staying true to RLCraft's origins, this will be a hardcore experience. Expect monsters to be faster, stronger, and smarter, expect to die frequently. Every step should be carefully planned by the player! This §eQuest Book §7will guide you through this entire journey - from§f §f§lzero §7to§f §lhero§7. Strap on your seat belts and steel your courage.

This §eQuest Book§7 will be given to you every time you die. Alternatively, press the §6Tilde §7or §6Grave§7 key on your keyboard (located immediately above §6TAB§7) to access it.

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
A campfire! This should allow me to cook food easily and keep me warm. Better watch my step around this thing, it would be a shame to get burned...


§7Can only cook §eRaw Food§7. Campfires will not burn out on its own. It will also instantly destroy any wooden item if thrown on it.

I will need some paper shreds as kindling to get a fire started, and later to make books.


§7Paper can be acquired in §2three§7 ways:

1. §eSugar Cane§7. Dig out the block below to harvest.

2. §eWildroot§7. This is acquired while collecting plant fibre with a §eKnife§7 and also when digging dirt and sand blocks.

3. §eBirch§7 bark is naturally a great material for this purpose.

Do I see any gravel pits nearby? 


§7Get some §eFlint§7 from gravel. This can then be turned into §eFlint Shards§7 by finding a hard surface like stone or cobblestone then §6right-clicking§7 it with §eFlint§7 in hand.

§7With the §9No Tree Punching §7mod, wood is gotten through other means than direct contact with fists. The goal is to collect enough materials to make a §eFlint Hatchet§7.

I will need some long-lasting fuel sources.


§7Acquiring §eANY §7of these items will complete the task.

The quality of these torches are horrible, but it's better than nothing...

§7
Torches from §9Realistic Torches§7 are unlit by default and must be lit either in the crafting grid or in-world by §eFlint and Steel§7 or §eMatchbox§7. They also eventually burn out and will need to be re-lit. It is advised to seek alternate sources of light as soon as possible: Use §9JEI §7to your advantage.
No Description

§fBuilding:§7 Those well-versed in building and §9Engineering§7 have an open-mind about the world and its complexities and always ready to innovate. They see each project as a new beginning and strive to achieve optimal results. From simple §eKilns§7 for alloying to §ePistons§7, from §eMetal Presses§7 to §eDrills§7, and it doesn't stop there; with §9Industrial §7prowess, §eAutomatic Mob Detectors§7, §eFluid Sieves§7 and even a §eDevice that Catches Creatures,§7 engineers §7improves§9 Quality §7of life and ensure safety for allies while guaranteeing destruction for their enemies.

Did I mention that you can also make §eguns§7? No? Now you know.

§7In addition to §9Reskillable §7skills, you can also invest §aexperience levels§7 to trade for skill points for the §9Level Up! Reloaded§7 §eSkill Book§7, which can be spent on directly boosting stats instead of unlocking more equipment. By default, §6B§7 is the keybind for this skills menu.

§fAgility:§7 Weapons that swing fast; typical "rogue" weapons such as rapiers, daggers, and ranged weapons such as bows and boomerangs.

Those favouring agility are no less cunning than the fox and no less agile than a cheetah. It makes no difference how strong an opponent is as long as the combatant is nigh untouchable. If the rogue does not make a fool of their enemies in a melee waltz of death, then a well-placed arrow from the dark would certainly finish the job.

Representative mods: §9Spartan Weaponry§7, §9Spartan Fire§7, §9Ice and Fire§7

Mining:§7 As simple as it sounds, the art of mining is used to extract precious resources from deep within the bowels of the earth. It might seem weak compared to the other skills, but you'll wish you hadn't thought this way when all of your tools can barely scratch the enemy; then you'll be begging for mercy yet will find none.

§fGathering:§7 Dictates all domains involving the collection and manipulation of earthly resources on the surface. Although primitive at first glance, those who master this art are self-sustaining and able to meet every challenge with an answer. Need healing? Drink an §eElixir§7. Need new tools and armor? The earth provides from the §9Roots§7 of the ancestor trees. §f§7Master §f§7gatherers are one with §9Nature §7and will fight with a varied arsenal from heavy armor to spells.

§fAttack:§7 Weapons that swing slow but hit hard; typical "fighter" weapons such as swords, pikes, and hammers. Crossbows use this stat heavily as well.

Those favouring attack tend to be fearsome warriors that relentlessly battle until it is won, rests for the evening, then goes to fight again come the morning. The best defense is a good offense when everyone the warrior meets falls over easily as snapping a twig in half.

Representative mods: §9Spartan Weaponry§7, §9Spartan Fire§7, §9Ice and Fire§7

Farming: §7Anything related to raising livestock, and growing crops. Crops, when harvested, have a chance of dropping §aexperience§7. Those who lie close to the §9Roots§7§7 of the earth and those who can feel the pulse of §9Nature's Aura§7 have vast knowledge reserves are masters of this craft. As the backbone of any community, farmers and their allies are never hungry.
No Description

§fMagic:§7 Anything that involves the enigmatic arcane energies, whether it be to harness the elements of §eSilver§7 and §eGold§7, or to devote oneself to studying the forbidden §9Wizardry§7 arts. §e§7Powerful scholars of magic§f§7 can §9§eEnchant§7 and §9Disenchant§7 items at will with §9Apotheotic§7 efficiency.

Magical elements are pervasive throughout the world. Don't make the mistake of discarding something unfamiliar just because you think it is "weak"!
I better know the basic mechanics of the game first!
No Description
